Site Reliability&amp;nbsp;Engineer&amp;nbsp;Excellent opportunity to be part of this high growth business unit transforming on premise applications to Google Cloud Platform.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;You will work with a dedicated team to design, configure, deploy, and support enterprise applications to GCP in a large, data intensive environment.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;RESPONSIBILITIES:&amp;nbsp;  - Work with business and IT team to transform enterprise applications from on prem to GCP   
  - Design, configure, deploy, and triage applications into production   
  - Code deployment utilizing terraform   
  - CI/CD&amp;nbsp;   
  - Write scripts, performance monitoring   
  - Support and on call duties&amp;nbsp;   
  - Document new processes   
   This is an excellent 6+ month contract opportunity working with&amp;nbsp;a high growth business unit as they transform to GCP. Outstanding opportunity to learn and grow your skills in a team that is seeking innovation in product and technology. Potential for conversion to full time employment. Ideally in Saint Louis or Atlanta but you can work 100% remotely.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;REQUIRED SKILLS:  - 5+ years as an SRE - Site Reliability Engineer&amp;nbsp;   
  - GCP - 1 year - experience deploying code to cloud platforms   
  - Experience deploying/supporting .Net/C# applications&amp;nbsp;   
  - Windows&amp;nbsp;and related scripting skills in PowerShell, Python, or Bash   
  - Knowledge of CI/CD, Jenkins pipelines   
  - Excellent troubleshooting skills and a problem-solver mindset   
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;PREFERRED SKILLS:  - Kubernetes - certifications&amp;nbsp;   
  - GKE&amp;nbsp;   
  - AppDynamics&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;   
